metadata.name: Diamond Twirl Composition #6
metadata.description:
Diamond Twirl Composition was inspired by a series of OP Art paintings done by Victor Vasarely, called Collage Vert (c. 1990). Vasarely died in 1997 in the early days of computer art. I'm sure he would have embraced this medium. This is the second in a series of Vasarely inspired Generative Art pieces I am offering.

I became interested in Victor Vasarely's graphic artworks while I was in art school. As I struggled to learn computer graphics I wondered how do I write a program to produce imagery with a similar aesthetic? I call the process of creating algorithms inspired by other artists: "Art"ificial Intelligence.

Diamond Twirl Composition is a regular grid of square tiles. The background of each square tile is filled with a random color. A coin-toss algorithm then decides whether to draw a diamond shaped polygon in its own random color leaning left or leaning right connected to opposite corner of the square tile background. Every iteration is unique and filled with energy. 

Dr. Bill Generative Art OG @ drbillkolomyjec.com

metadata.name: Tesseract #273
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #89
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

S : display stats

metadata.name: Miniscapes #353
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: The Face We Had #140
metadata.description:
The Face We Had is a series of generative, moving sculptures attempting to express the artists personal thoughts, experiences and inclinations related to meditative and altered states of consciousness. In a non-descriptive way, the piece aims to reflect the always changing nature of mind through patterns of movement and assemblages of form, color and organic shapes, endlessly revolving around a perceived point of origin.  

Although not intended as literal depictions, the elements interact in a way that could be interpreted as dance-like interactions between thought patterns, mental energy, feelings, fragments of memories and layers of personal identity. 



Interactive features:

space - pause/play
w - wireframe view
d - debug view (compute textures)
s - save screenshot

metadata.name: glory hole$ #189
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.

metadata.name: ‚ÄòLow-Res‚Äô poems #34
metadata.description:
‚ÄòLow-Res‚Äô poems is a collection as a high-tech alternative search. It was made with two free small, lightweight softwares like kidpix.app and magicavoxel, using the @PureSpider template to create iterations. This collection  is produced from technological limitations, a socioeconomic condition implies a determined political position and this is reflected on the access to technology, mainly the access to hardware.
As an artist, not having access to specialized high-tech hardware and software made my workflow, or the way I approach art, different, putting me in a place where I had to open myself and embrace low-poly or low-res alternatives to continue making art.

‚ÄòLow-Res‚Äô has 50 MagicaVoxel models in 3D and 6 backgrounds made in kidpix.app, in each piece, the features combinations build corny poems, which give each piece an unique spirit and name. These poems work as a continuation of the Digital Collage collection.

High res tech has often been a vector of cultural hegemony over the global south, especially in terms of access to the tech- Sabatobox @sabatobox

metadata.name: Saccharin #86
metadata.description:
A continuation of my previous work but with a more minimalistic visual approach. Randomly generated primitive geometry are rendered as texture that undergoes a series of nodes to create a grayscale image. The texture is then colored with gradient map, layered with pixel noise to divide it into a randomly sized grid then subtly blurred in some areas to create a dreamy effect.

The resulting visual can seem vaguely familiar but at the same time can not be pinpointed to a specific time and place identity; it can vary between a Futurist painting look-alike to resembling an early 2000s colorful news bumper. Hazy memory slowly and constantly shifting, clouded vision taste artificially sweet, sometimes with a metallic aftertaste.

Just like saccharin.

----------
